<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05074l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05074l">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05074l"> 74(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> energetics</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It will be noticed that my formula <font color="green">[that language ranks highest which goes the farthest in the art of accomplishing much with little means, or, in other words, which is able to express the greatest amount of meaning with the simplest mechanism]</font> contains two requirements: it demands a maximum of efficiency and a minimum of effort. Efficiency means expressiveness, and effort means bodily and mental labours, and thus the formula is simply one of modern <mark>energetics</mark>. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJLN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#OJLN"><cite title="source">Language: its Nature, Development and Origin</cite></a> (Jan 1922) 324</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Upside down.</mm> </dd></dl>
